messages.content: Its the card that makes the bot shid itself
too many upgrades ig

Haven't played with this much since it was updated to no longer give the enemy's strength. It's a very small amount of offensive and defensive scaling, and even though champ struggles with both of those things in the late game, you would rather have higher impact cards solve those problems, like gladiator form, strike of genius, and iron fortress. If your deck has a lot of card draw (unlikely on champ) and you are getting these freely upgraded (frozen egg or getting lucky), then I don't mind taking several of them, since your early game is strong enough that you don't tend to get too punished for taking scaling/low impact cards on champ early in the run. Unupgraded though, this card is really low impact, and difficult to justify taking unless you are really struggling to find scaling. 

Only good into 1 of the act 1 elites, and it will probably get in the way of the demanding act 2 hallway fights that call for more immediately impactful cards. The strength gain is pretty useful, since champ has so many multi hit cards to pair with vigor, but you can also more easily gain strength by playing a finisher in berserker stance. Can get a lot better with mummified hand, bolster rod, or bird faced urn, since it's so cheap and can easily proc their effects. 

Flavorwise, the card is quite bland, I much preferred the flavor of the old version that gave the enemy strength and radiated that overconfidant vibe. Mechanically, it's really boring and doesn't really tie very well into champs synergies. I feel like this card doesn't really fit well for champ, and should be reworked, though I understand that champ is already lined up for major reworks due to their insane early game numbers
